# Banking Project - Cursor AI Agent Rules (Canonical)

> Project: Next.js 16, TypeScript (strict), Drizzle ORM, PostgreSQL, NextAuth, shadcn/UI, Tailwind CSS v4

Last Updated: 2026-04-11

Purpose

- Short, machine-friendly reference for automated agents (Cursor/OpenCode) to consult before making edits or running commands.
- Defer to `AGENTS.md` for expanded guidance. When in doubt, follow executable sources of truth (package.json, eslint.config.mts, app-config.ts/lib/env.ts).

Critical Rules (PR-blocking)

- No `any` types — use `unknown` + type guards. TypeScript strict is enforced.
- No N+1 queries — eager load relations with JOINs; do not query inside loops.
- Do not read `process.env` directly in application code; use `app-config.ts` or `lib/env.ts`.
- All stateful mutations must be Server Actions (`actions/`).
- Zero TypeScript errors and zero ESLint warnings (`npm run lint:strict`) before PR.

Quick Commands

- `npm run dev` — Start dev server
- `npm run build` — Production build
- `npm run type-check` — Run TypeScript checks
- `npm run lint:strict` — Run strict ESLint (0 warnings)
- `npm run test` — Run tests (E2E first, then unit)

Project Structure (important paths)

- `app/` — Next.js App Router routes
-- `actions/` — Server Actions (mutations)
-- `dal/` — Data Access Layer (all DB access)
- `database/` — Drizzle schema and db connection
- `.opencode/` — Agent skills and instructions

When Docs Conflict

- Prefer executable sources of truth. Update prose to match and record the decision in `.opencode/plans/`.

Checklist for agents (minimal)

1. Read `package.json` scripts and `eslint.config.mts` before running lint or changing lint configs.
2. Create a plan in `.opencode/plans/` if a change touches more than 3 files.
3. Run `npm run format`, `npm run type-check`, and `npm run lint:strict` before committing.

End of .cursorrules

Note: This file is synchronized with AGENTS.md. See plan: `.opencode/plans/update-agentic-docs_4f7a8b2c.plan.md`.
